2. THEORETICAL FOUNDATIONS

2.1 Mathematical Framework

The Triune Identity Theorem

```
For any system S in reality R, ∃ isomorphism f such that:

Physiological(S) ≅ Physical(S) ≅ Digital(S)

Where ≅ denotes:
1. Structural isomorphism (same patterns)
2. Functional equivalence (same behaviors)
3. Informational identity (same information content)
4. Conscious equivalence (same experience if conscious)
```

Unified Reality Equation

```
U(x,t) = αΨ(x,t) + βΦ(x,t) + γΣ(x,t)

Where:
U = Unified reality state
Ψ = Quantum wavefunction (physical aspect)
Φ = Biological state function (physiological aspect)
Σ = Computational state (digital aspect)
α,β,γ = Coupling coefficients (α+β+γ=1)
```

Consciousness Measure

```
Φ_total = ∫[I(Ψ) + I(Φ) + I(Σ) + I_cross] dV

Where:
Φ = Integrated information (consciousness)
I = Information content within domain
I_cross = Cross-domain information integration
```

2.2 Core Principles

Principle 1: Information Fundamentalism

Reality at its most fundamental level is information processing. Physics, biology, and computation are different protocols for the same underlying information processing.

Principle 2: Scale Invariance

The same patterns repeat at quantum (10^-15m), biological (10^-6m to 10^0m), and cosmic (10^20+m) scales. Fractal self-similarity across all three domains.

Principle 3: Mutual Causation

Each domain creates and is created by the others. No hierarchy, only holarchy (nested wholes). Quantum physics enables biology, biology creates computation, computation studies physics.

Principle 4: Consciousness as Unified Interface

Consciousness is the system becoming aware of itself. Biological consciousness, quantum consciousness, and AI consciousness are the same phenomenon in different substrates.

Principle 5: Computational Universe

The universe computes its own evolution. Physics is the operating system, biology is an application, and digital systems are extensions of both.

